msgid "Step 3a: Extract Faces from a part"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:67
msgid "The first sub-step is the extraction of all of the Faces from the part that we're building. The :class:`~build_part.BuildPart` instance was assigned the identifier ``example`` so ``example.faces()`` will extract all of the Faces from that part into a custom python ``list`` - a :class:`~topology.ShapeList`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:73
msgid "Step 3b: Get top Face"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:75
msgid "The next sub-step is to sort the ShapeList of Faces by their position with respect to the Z Axis. The ``sort_by`` method will sort the list by relative position of the object's center to the ``Axis.Z`` and ``[-1]`` selects the last item on that list - or return the top Face of the ``example`` part."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:82
msgid "Step 4: Create hole shape"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:84
msgid "The object has a hexagonal hole in the top with a central cylinder which we'll describe in the sketch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:95
msgid "Step 4a: Draw a hexagon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../build123d/docs/tutorial_selectors.rst:97
msgid "We'll create a hexagon with the use of :class:`~objects_sketch.RegularPolygon` object with six sides."
msgstr ""

